 of the COVID-19 disease in the Czech Republic|date=|website=onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Week 9 (24 February \u2013 1 March)===\n'''28 February''' \u2013\nAs of 28 February 170 suspected cases were tested with negative results. 307 people were in home [[quarantine]] imposed by a regional health authority, 77 of them were in [[South Bohemian Region]].<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n'''1 March''' \u2013\nThe [[Ministry of Health (Czech Republic)|Minister of Health]], [[Adam Vojt\u011bch]], reported that three cases of COVID-19 had been confirmed by the National Reference Laboratory.<ref name=\"case1-3\">{{cite news|url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/domaci/3056228-v-cesku-jsou-tri-lide-nakazeni-koronavirem|title=V \u010cesku jsou t\u0159i lid\u00e9 naka\u017een\u00ed koronavirem. P\u0159edt\u00edm byli v It\u00e1lii|date=|work=\u010cT24|access-date=|url-status=live|language=cs}}</ref> The three cases are treated at the [[Bulovka Hospital]] in Prague; one of the cases had been found in [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]], but was transported to the Bulovka Hospital.<ref name=case1-3/> All cases were connected with northern Italy. One case was a man who returned from a conference in [[Udine]], the second case was a woman (tourist, U.S. citizen) studying in [[Milan]] and the third case was a man who returned from a skiing holiday in [[Auronzo di Cadore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/domaci/v-cesku-se-objevily-prvni-pripady-koronaviru-dva-jsou-v-praz/r~3eb53e385bd011eaaabd0cc47ab5f122/|title=V \u010cesku se objevily prvn\u00ed p\u0159\u00edpady koronaviru. V\u0161ichni p\u0159ijeli ze severn\u00ed It\u00e1lie {{!}} Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz|date=1 March 2020|website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz \u2013 V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje|language=cs|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/akademik-lyzar-a-studentka-z-italie-kdo-je-trojice-nakazenych-v-cesku-90690|title=Akademik, ly\u017ea\u0159 a studentka z It\u00e1lie. Kdo je trojice naka\u017een\u00fdch v \u010cesku? \u2013 Seznam Zpr\u00e1vy|website=seznamzpravy.cz|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Week 10 (2 \u2013 8 March)===\n'''2 March''' \u2013\nAnother case was confirmed, a woman who was on skiing holiday in Auronzo di Cadore and was staying in the same hotel as the man from a previous case.<ref name=\"case4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/cesko-ma-ctvrty-pripad-nakazy-koronavirem-40315302|title=\u010cesko m\u00e1 \u010dtvrt\u00fd p\u0159\u00edpad n\u00e1kazy koronavirem |website=novinky.cz |language=cs |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''3 March''' \u2013\nAnother case was reported, a woman from Ecuador studying in Milano, a friend of the U.S. tourist who tested positive several days prior.<ref name=\"case5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/paty-pripad-koronaviru-v-cesku-zena-z-ekvadoru-mela-prvni-test-negativni-40315311|title=P\u00e1t\u00fd p\u0159\u00edpad koronaviru v \u010cesku. \u017dena p\u0159itom m\u011bla prvn\u00ed test negativn\u00ed |website=novinky.cz |language=cs |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment started taking active measures (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).\n\n'''5 March''' \u2013\nFour new cases were identified a Czech and an Italian who returned from Italy by end of February, third was related to case No. 3 and fourth was related to case No. 6.<ref name=\"case9-12\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus.A200305_142537_domaci_remy|title=Po\u010det naka\u017een\u00fdch koronavirem stoupl na 12, mezi nimi mu\u017e a d\u00edt\u011b z Prahy|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''6 March''' \u2013\nObligatory 14 days quarantine for people returning from selected parts of Italy announced (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/coronavirus-czechs-returning-from-italy-to-stay-in-two-week-quarantine|title=Coronavirus: Czechs returning from Italy to stay in two-week quarantine|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Cizinci/dokumenty/ministry-of-health-issues-an-extraordinary-measure-of-quarantine-for-persons-ret_18656_2649_23.html|title=Ministry of Health Issues an Extraordinary Measure of Quarantine for Persons Returning from Italy|website=mzcr.cz|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> As of 6 March 1,011 people were already in home quarantine imposed by regional health authority, 341 of them in Prague, 160 in [[South Bohemian Region]] and 63 in [[Central Bohemian Region]].<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n===Week 11 (9 \u2013 15 March)===\n'''9 March''' \u2013 Bulovka Hospital in [[Prague]] has announced that all but two tourists (from U.S. \u2013 case No. 2 and from Ecuador \u2013 case #5) have been released to home quarantine.<ref name=\"mar09.BulovkaRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/nemocnice-na-bulovce-koronavirus-briefing-stav-budov-rohacova-kvacek.A200309_102455_domaci_kane|title=Na Bulovce z\u016fstaly dv\u011b cizinky. Jsou to sp\u00ed\u0161e klientky, \u0159ekla prim\u00e1\u0159ka|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''10 March''' \u2013\nPositive cases were being identified in ever increasing number of regions.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/koronavirus-2019-ncov-aktualni-data_18455_4122_1.html|title=COVID-19: Aktu\u00e1ln\u00ed po\u010dty onemocn\u011bn\u00ed koronavirem v \u010cR|website=mzcr.cz|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> The Czech Republic became one of the first{{failed verification|date=April 2020}} countries in EU to close its schools.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/coronavirus-all-czech-schools-unis-to-close-as-of-wednesday|title=Coronavirus: Czech schools close, large events banned|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''11 March''' \u2013\nA first patient with COVID-19 reached state that required an intensive care unit.{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''12 March''' \u2013\n[[Government of the Czech Republic|The Czech government]] has declared a [[state of emergency]] for 30 days and adopted a number of measures (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/cz/media-centrum/aktualne/vyhlaseni-nouzoveho-stavu-180234/|title=Vyhl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu|website=vlada.cz|language=cs|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-government-declares-state-of-emergency-in-response-to-coronavirus-epidemic|title=Czech government declares state of emergency in response to coronavirus epidemic|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''13 March''' \u2013\nBrno University Hospital (a COVID-19 testing center) was [[Cybercrime|hacked]], disrupting services.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cimpanu |first1=Catalin |title=Czech hospital hit by cyberattack while in the midst of a COVID-19 outbreak |url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/czech-hospital-hit-by-cyber-attack-while-in-the-midst-of-a-covid-19-outbreak/ |publisher=ZDNet  |date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/domaci/3061748-fakultni-nemocnice-v-brne-celi-kybernetickemu-utoku-pise-idnescz|title=Z\u00e1kladn\u00ed provoz nemocnice v Brn\u011b i po kybernetick\u00e9m \u00fatoku funguje, \u0159ekl \u0159editel|date=|website=\u010cT24|language=cs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n'''15 March''' \u2013\nShortly before midnight, Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] announced approval of the nationwide quarantine (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).\n\n===Week 12 (16 \u2013 22 March)===\n'''16 March''' \u2013\nStarting at midnight, an hour after the nationwide quarantine declaration was approved the previous day, nearly 11&nbsp;million Czech residents were placed under quarantine (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).<ref name=\"apnews\">{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/16c6a936bd0eecd81d468a993f182890|title=The Latest: Peru, Honduras enacting new containment measures|date=15 March 2020|website=AP NEWS|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref> The Czech Republic became one of the first<ref>{{cite web|author=Tamara Thiessen |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarathiessen/2020/03/14/coronavirus-europe-closes-borders-tourists/ |title=Coronavirus: Some Of These 24 European Countries Have Closed Their Borders To Tourists |work=Forbes |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> countries in the EU to completely close its borders (with exemptions including international freight transport, see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).<ref name=\"apnews\"/> First three people were reported recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=Breaking: Czech Republic reports first three cases of coronavirus recovery \u2013 Prague, Czech Republic |url=https://news.expats.cz/weekly-czech-news/breaking-czech-republic-reports-first-three-cases-of-coronavirus-recovery/ |website=Expats.cz Latest News & Articles \u2013 Prague and the Czech Republic |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> \n\n'''18 March''' \u2013\nThe Czech Republic became the first<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.praguemorning.cz/could-czechs-measure-to-fight-coronavirus-save-thousands-of-lives-2/ |title=Could Czech's Measure to Fight Coronavirus Save Thousands of Lives? |publisher=Praguemorning.cz |date=4 April 2020 |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> country in the EU to introduce mandatory face cover (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).<ref name=\"march18.radio.cz\">{{cite news|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/government-bans-going-out-without-covered-mouth-and-nose|title=Government bans going out without covered mouth and nose|date=18 March 2020|work=radio.cz|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''21 March''' \u2013\nDeliveries of protective gear purchased by Czech Government in China started: a heavy cargo plane [[Antonov An-124]] provided through [[NATO Support and Procurement Agency]] brought 100 tons of masks, respirators and coronavirus tests from China, while a China Eastern plane brought seven million facemasks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/two-planeloads-of-protective-gear-arrive-from-china|title=Two planeloads of protective gear arrive from China|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> This helped to alleviate the shortage of personal protective equipment (PPE) in the Czech Republic. According to [[Security Information Service]], the shortage happened after Chinese embassy conducted massive purchases of respirators available on Czech market during January and February and transferred them to China.<ref name=\"BIS report\"/>\n\n'''22 March''' \u2013\n'''First death reported''': a 95-year-old man.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/coronavirus-cases-now-over-1000|title=Czech Republic has first coronavirus-related death|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> While COVID-19 positive, at the time of death, the man was not at [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] and did not suffer from pneumonia that is a COVID-19 specific type of death. The man suffered from chronical heart issues and had also a pacemaker. The cause of death was formally established as a \"complete exhaustion of organism\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/domaci/prvni-obet-koronaviru-v-cesku-trpela-radou-nemoci/r~e5cf5dec6c7a11ea842f0cc47ab5f122/|title=\"Zem\u0159el sp\u00ed\u0161 s koronavirem ne\u017e na n\u011bj.\" Prvn\u00ed mrtv\u00fd v \u010cesku trp\u011bl \u0159adou nemoc\u00ed|date=22 March 2020|website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz|language=cs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Week 13 (23 \u2013 29 March)===\n'''23 March''' \u2013\nThe local health authority in the [[Moravian-Silesian Region]] announced that 80% of COVID-19 examinations that were conducted in the region in the previous days with use of fast-test kits that government procured and airlifted from China (altogether 300,000 kits bought by the Czech Government for total price of CZK 54 m \u2013 approx. US$2.1 m) came out wrong when double-checked through standard testing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-ostrava-hygienicka-rychlotesty.A200323_121144_domaci_bur|title=Rychlotesty nejsou k plo\u0161n\u00e9mu u\u017eit\u00ed, slou\u017e\u00ed jen u rizikov\u00fdch skupin|date=23 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/prymula-o-chybovosti-rychlotestu-jsme-vedeli-menime-narizeni-40317761|title=Prymula: O chybovosti rychlotest\u016f jsme v\u011bd\u011bli. M\u011bn\u00edme na\u0159\u00edzen\u00ed |website=novinky.cz |language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\nIt was later confirmed the cause was an incorrect use where the fast-test react to an immune response and are not suitable for new patient screenings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/rychlotesty-z-ciny-maji-chybovost-80-procent-tvrdi-hygienici-40317721|title=Rychlotesty z \u010c\u00edny lze pou\u017e\u00edt a\u017e po n\u011bkolika dnech od n\u00e1kazy|date=23 March 2020|website=novinky.cz|access-date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''24 March''' \u2013\nA second death was reported: a 45-year-old man died after six days in a hospital in [[Hav\u00ed\u0159ov]]. The patient was suffering from advanced cancer with metastases to multiple organs. The cause of death was established as multiple organ failure due to cancer but COVID-19 infection accelerated the patient's death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/hradec-kralove/zpravy/fakultni-nemocnice-hradec-kralove-koronavirus.A200324_112700_hradec-zpravy_alh|title=Koronavirus na hematologick\u00e9 klinice. V karant\u00e9n\u011b jsou zam\u011bstnanci i pacienti|date=24 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nA third death was reported: a 71-year-old woman died in V\u0161eobecn\u00e1 fakultn\u00ed nemocnice in Prague. The woman suffered from the chronic obstructive pulmonary disease as well as other illnesses, so it wasn't immediately clear that she may be COVID-19 positive. Only after being hospitalised the woman informed doctors that her relative recently returned from Italy and was then tested for COVID-19. The woman was connected to a ventilator but died three days after start of hospitalisation.<ref name=\"third death\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/covid-19-koronavirus-v-cesku-treti-obet-pacient-vfn-vseobecna-fakultni-nemocnice-praha-umrti-smrt.A200324_211635_domaci_elka|title=T\u0159et\u00ed \u010deskou ob\u011bt\u00ed koronaviru je 71let\u00e1 \u017eena, nakazila se od p\u0159\u00edbuzn\u00e9|date=24 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nApart from the Uber driver on ECMO, there were 19 other patients in hospitals in serious condition, all of them connected to ventilators.<ref name=\"third death\"/>\n\n'''25 March''' \u2013\nA fourth and fifth death was reported: The fourth victim of the disease is a 82-year-old from Prague with long-term chronic health problems. The fifth patient is a 88-year-old man from the Central Bohemian Region who was at home getting treatment and was suffering from a chronic disease.<ref name=\"seznamzpravy.cz\">{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/nenavstevujte-prarodice-vyzval-vojtech-zemrelou-seniorku-nakazili-pribuzni-95555|title=V Krumlov\u011b je deset naka\u017een\u00fdch, klienti i person\u00e1l soci\u00e1ln\u00ed slu\u017eby|date=|website=Seznam Zpr\u00e1vy|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nA sixth patient died at [[Thomayer Hospital]]. The 75-year-old patient suffered from diabetes and [[Parkinson's disease]] and also had advanced heart problems. The patient had been in the hospital since January and got infected while in post-operative care. After this patient tested positive for COVID-19, the hospital tested all 29 other patients in the same ward on 22 March, all negative. The test was repeated again on 25 March, this time with positive outcomes for 13 patients. Several of the hospital's staff had become infected earlier, probably while taking care of the [[Uber]] driver who would later become the first [[remdesivir]] receiver in the country. This patient was originally admitted with simple pneumonia without initial indication of COVID-19. Two of the infected nurses were hospitalised at the local pulmonary ward at the time of the sixth patient's death.<ref name=\"seznamzpravy.cz\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/v-nemocnici-kde-zemrel-muz-s-koronavirem-je-nakazeno-13-senioru-40318095|title=V pra\u017esk\u00e9 nemocnici, kde zem\u0159el mu\u017e s koronavirem, je naka\u017eeno 13 senior\u016f|date=|website=Novinky.cz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe government was planning to evacuate Czechs from Australia and New Zealand by the end of the week. Hundreds of Czechs still remained abroad, mainly in Oceania and Southeast Asia.<ref name=\"seznamzpravy.cz\"/>\n\nAn [[Antonov An-124]] provided through the [[NATO Support and Procurement Agency]] arrived again with 24 tons of medical products purchased by the Czech government in China. The shipment included 52,600 protective suits, 70,900 protective glasses, 250,000 gloves, 1,160,000 respirators and eight million masks. Further government purchased personal protection equipment shipments were planned for delivery with use of planes by the companies [[Smartwings]] and [[China Eastern]], which were contracted for nine flights per week for six weeks in advance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/v-mosnove-a-parubicich-pristala-letadla-s-materialem-z-ciny/1871084|title=V Mo\u0161nov\u011b a Parubic\u00edch p\u0159ist\u00e1la letadla s materi\u00e1lem z \u010c\u00edny|date=|website=\u010cesk\u00e9Noviny.cz|language=cs|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n<div style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 0.5em 1em; width: 30em; text-align: right; font-size: 0.86em; font-family: lucida grande, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\">\n<div style=\"border:1px solid #999; background:#fff; text-align:left; padding:1em; text-align:left;\">'''Pendlers'''<br>\n\n37,000 and 13,000 Czechs live in the Czech Republic and work in Germany and Austria respectively, large portion of that in healthcare.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/ekonomika/2912609-za-praci-dojizdi-do-ciziny-pres-56-tisic-cechu-nejvic-do-nemecka-miri-ale-i-do|title=Za prac\u00c3\u00ad doj\u00c3\u00ad\u00c5\u00bed\u00c3\u00ad do ciziny p\u00c5\u0099es 56 tis\u00c3\u00adc \u00c4\u008cech\u00c5\u00af. Nejv\u00c3\u00adc do N\u00c4\u009bmecka, m\u00c3\u00ad\u00c5\u0099\u00c3\u00ad ale i do Brit\u00c3\u00a1nie \u00e2\u0080\u0094 \u00c4\u008cT24 \u00e2\u0080\u0094 \u00c4\u008cesk\u00c3\u00a1 televize}}</ref> Cross-border workers (pendlers) were originally exempted from the complete travel ban. As Germany and Austria gradually became major centers of COVID-19 outbreak, the Government started tightening up rules for pendlers. By 26 March, Czechs commuting to work in Austria and Germany were required to remain in those countries for at least 21 days. Upon return, they would be quarantined for 14 days. Czechs working in health, social services, and emergency services abroad were not subject to the new rules.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/new-rules-apply-for-czechs-commuting-for-work-in-austria-germany|title=New rules apply for Czechs commuting for work in Austria, Germany|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mvcr.cz/mvcren/article/coronavirus-information-of-moi.aspx |title=Coronavirus \u2013 Information of MoI \u2013 Ministry of the interior of the Czech Republic |publisher=Mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The rules were eased from 14 April onwards (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).\n\nDistricts bordering Germany and Austria gradually became major centers of COVID19 outbreak in the Czech Republic. [[Doma\u017elice District]] reached the highest number of COVID19 positive persons relative to population size in the country. According to Vice-prime Minister Czech government avoided closing the pendler loophole because German and Austrian healthcare system in areas close to the border is dependant on Czech pendlers and also because government feared it could lead Slovakia to close access to Slovak pendlers working in Czech healthcare.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/domazlice-pendleri-koronavirus-nakaza-sireni-cesty-omezeni-kraj-ustredni-krizovy_2004081059_tzr|title=Epidemie na Doma\u017elicku p\u0159ed\u010dila Prahu. Podle hygienik\u016f \u0161\u00ed\u0159\u00ed n\u00e1kazu zdravotn\u00edci pendluj\u00edc\u00ed do N\u011bmecka|website=iROZHLAS}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/koronavirus-v-cesku-pendleri-ministerstvo-vnitra_2003252008_pj|title=V\u00fdjimka pro pendlery. P\u0159\u00edsn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed pravidla se nedotknou lid\u00ed ve zdravotnictv\u00ed \u010di soci\u00e1ln\u00edch slu\u017eb\u00e1ch|website=iROZHLAS}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/plzen/zpravy/domazlicko-karantena-koronavirus-sireni.A200409_183516_plzen-zpravy_zuf|title=Doma\u017elicko kv\u016fli koronaviru zat\u00edm plo\u0161n\u00e1 karant\u00e9na ne\u010dek\u00e1|date=9 April 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES}}</ref> </div></div>\n'''26 March''' \u2013\nA Taiwanese student in her twenties, who recently returned to Taiwan from the Czech Republic tested positive for coronavirus. She left the Czech Republic after 8 months in the country on 19 March 2020, announced symptoms (fever, diarrhoea) to Taiwanese authorities on 24 March and was diagnosed COVID-19 positive on 26 March 2020.<ref>\u6848236\u81f3252\u4f8b\u78ba\u8a3a [https://www.cdc.gov.tw/File/Get/INETA_ZtvnuHsFt1TjrQdQ \u65b0\u589e17\u4f8b\u78ba\u8a3a\uff0c15\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u79fb\u5165\u30012\u4f8b\u672c\u571f] \u4e2d\u592e\u6d41\u884c\u75ab\u60c5\u6307\u63ee\u4e2d\u5fc3 26 March 2020</ref> 34 patients were in severe condition.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/od-rana-se-znovu-oteviraji-nektere-prodejny-96045|title=Babi\u0161 chce v \u010cesku prodlou\u017eit nouzov\u00fd stav, po\u010det naka\u017een\u00fdch stoupl na 2279|date=|website=Seznam Zpr\u00e1vy|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''27 March''' \u2013\nDespite having been quarantined already for two weeks, at least six retirement homes were hit by the spread of the COVID-19 virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-domovy-senioru-opatreni-zprisneni-socialni-sluzby.A200327_163825_domaci_aug|title=Koronavirus u\u017e zas\u00e1hl \u0161est domov\u016f pro seniory. Izolovat v\u00edc nezvl\u00e1d\u00e1me, \u0159\u00edkaj\u00ed|date=27 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Authorities noted also the rising number of COVID-19 positive healthcare workers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-seniori-nakazeni-cesky-krumlov.A200327_540920_ekonomika_lesa|title=Naka\u017een\u00ed senio\u0159i: nejhor\u0161\u00ed sc\u00e9n\u00e1\u0159. V domovech jich onemocn\u011bly des\u00edtky|date=27 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> As the capacity for COVID-19 testing increased, authorities eased requirements for free testing. Anyone with a fever, dry cough or shortness of breath may be eligible for a free COVID-19 test.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-testovani-covid-19-horecka-kasel-dusnost-doporuceni-pacient-nakazeny-mrtvi.A200327_170734_domaci_rapc|title=\u010cesko m\u00e1 2 279 naka\u017een\u00fdch. Nov\u011b sta\u010d\u00ed k testu hore\u010dka, such\u00fd ka\u0161el \u010di du\u0161nost|date=27 March 2020|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''29 March''' \u2013\nFive people died. Among the victims was a 45-year-old nurse from Thomayer Hospital, an elderly woman from a senior home in Michle and an elderly woman from a senior home in B\u0159evnice. There were 227 patients in hospitals, 45 of them in severe condition.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/v-cesku-je-2663-nakazenych-koronavirem-96462 |title=Zem\u0159ela zdravotn\u00ed sestra z Thomayerovy nemocnice |publisher=Seznamzpravy.cz |date=29 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Week 14 (30 March \u2013 5 April)===\n'''30 March''' \u2013\nIn [[South Moravia]], testing of the so-called \"smart quarantine\" was started: local travel history of infected persons were to be tracked using data from mobile phones and bank cards. 300 military personnel were deployed to reinforce local health authority for the purpose of tracing patients' contacts and collecting samples. If this approach is deemed successful by the authorities for diminishing the pandemic, the \"smart quarantine\" method is planned to replace the existing nationwide curfew policy.<ref>{{cite web|author=Martin Proch\u00e1zka|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/chytra-karantena-se-zacne-testovat-na-jihu-moravy-jak-bude-fungovat-40318396 |title=Chytr\u00e1 karant\u00e9na se za\u010dne testovat na jihu Moravy. Jak bude fungovat? |publisher=Novinky.cz |date=28 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The city of [[Uhersk\u00fd Brod]] started thorough disinfection of all common areas of apartment buildings and public areas after a significant increase in COVID-19 infections. Health authority registered thirty new cases in the town.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/on-line-v-cr-je-uz-2817-infikovanych-koronavirem-40318526 |title=V \u010cesku je 3001 naka\u017een\u00fdch koronavirem |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''31 March''' \u2013\nIn a community of 72 people living in a retirement home in [[Litom\u011b\u0159ice]], 52 positive tests were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seznamzpravy.cz/clanek/pripadu-koronaviru-v-cr-v-pondeli-pribylo-184-je-jich-pres-3000-96922 |title=\u010cesko m\u00e1 3257 naka\u017een\u00fdch, 31 lid\u00ed zem\u0159elo|publisher=Seznamzpravy.cz |date=31 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\nEmployees of the retirement home in [[\u010cesk\u00e1 Kamenice]] decided to stay with their clients 24 hours a day until 15 April, to avoid the seniors getting COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web | author=NasRegion.cz | title=Nebudou chodit dom\u016f. Rozhodly se pracovnice domova senior\u016f | website=N\u00e1\u0161 REGION | date=31 March 2020 | url=https://nasregion.cz/decinsko/nebudou-chodit-domu-rozhodly-se-pracovnice-domova-senioru/ | language=cs | access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n<div style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 0.5em 1em; width: 30em; text-align: right; font-size: 0.86em; font-family: lucida grande, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\">\n<div style=\"border:1px solid #999; background:#fff; text-align:left; padding:1em; text-align:left;\">'''Czech aid to other countries'''\n* '''China''': On 17 February, a plane with 4,5 tons of personal protection equipment donated by Czech Government left from Vienna to China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/zive-ministr-petricek-k-humanitarni-pomoci-cine-na-boj-s-koronavirem-40313332 |title=Respir\u00e1tory, rou\u0161ky, rukavice. \u010cesko pos\u00edl\u00e1 do \u010c\u00edny 4,5 tuny materi\u00e1ln\u00ed pomoci |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The plane was also loaded with Hungarian, Slovak and Austrian PPE donations to China. \n* '''China''': On 1 March, a plane with 5 tons of PPE (including 780.000 pairs of gloves, 48.000 facemasks and 6.800 protection suits) left from Prague to China. This time the load was donated by a multitude of parties, including President's Office, Olomouc Region, Karlovy Vary Region, South Moravian Region, Vyso\u010dina Region, the town of T\u0159eb\u00ed\u010d and [[\u0160koda Auto]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Ji\u0159\u00ed Ov\u010d\u00e1\u010dek (Twitter) |url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/letste-kbely-armadni-special-pomoc-cina-humantni-pomoc-koronavirus.A200301_091014_zahranicni_lre |title=\u010cesko poslalo do \u010c\u00edny speci\u00e1l s humanit\u00e1rn\u00ed pomoc\u00ed. Ze Kbel odlet\u011bl v noci |work=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES |date=27 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The donation was too large to fit into a single plane and thus there were further flights planned. Those however did not take place, as China declined to accept the aid.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/zdravotnicky-material-humanitarni-pomoc-cina-koronavirus-cesko.A200310_144531_domaci_tho |title=\u010c\u00edna v\u011bnovala \u010cesku zp\u011bt humanit\u00e1rn\u00ed pomoc, kter\u00e1 se neve\u0161la do letadla |work=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES |date=27 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* '''Italy''': Czech Government donated 110,000 FFP2 respirators to Italy on 23 March. This donation took place after Czech authorities confiscated 680,000 respirators from a fraudster, who was stockpiling them in a warehouse in [[Lovosice]]. According to media, 110,000 of the confiscated respirators were originally sent from China as a donation to the 300,000 strong Chinese minority that lives in Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jan Mol\u00e1\u010dek |url=https://denikn.cz/321235/stat-zabavil-i-respiratory-ktere-posilal-cerveny-kriz-na-pomoc-italii-bylo-to-nedorozumeni-rika-hamacek/ |title=St\u00e1t zabavil i respir\u00e1tory, kter\u00e9 pos\u00edlal \u010cerven\u00fd k\u0159\u00ed\u017e na pomoc It\u00e1lii. Bylo to nedorozum\u011bn\u00ed, \u0159\u00edk\u00e1 Ham\u00e1\u010dek \u2013 Den\u00edk N |publisher=Denikn.cz |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/za-rousky-zabavene-v-lovosicich-daruje-cesko-do-italie-jine-40317709 |title=Za rou\u0161ky zabaven\u00e9 v Lovosic\u00edch \"daruje\" \u010cesko do It\u00e1lie jin\u00e9 |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* '''Italy, Spain''': 10,000 protective suits were donated to Italy and Spain each on 26 March (delivered on 30 March).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/coronavirus-czech-state-to-offer-italy-and-spain-10000-protective-suits|title=Coronavirus: Czech state to offer Italy and Spain 10,000 protective suits|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''Slovenia''': One million face masks and 200.000 FFP2 respirators were donated to [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Slovenia|to Slovenia]] on 1 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://denikn.cz/minuta/331892/ |title=Do Slovinska dorazil z \u010ceska milion chirurgick\u00fdch masek a 200 000 respir\u00e1tor\u016f FFP2 |publisher=Denikn.cz |date=1 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* '''France''': Czech Republic offered treatment of French COVID-19 patients in serious condition. First six patients were to be airlifted from France on 6 April and placed at University Hospital in [[Brno]].<ref name=\"ceskenoviny1\">{{cite web|author=Autor: <!-- Pole autor --> \u010cTK |url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/cr-prijme-pacienty-z-francie-obchody-a-sportoviste-asi-od-ctvrtka/1876003 |title=\u010cR p\u0159ijme pacienty z Francie, obchody a sportovi\u0161t\u011b asi od \u010dtvrtka |work=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> On the day of the planned airlift, however, France declined the help, stating that it is now able to better deal with the pandemic on its own.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/sestice-francouzu-s-koronavirem-prileti-do-brna-specialem-v-pondeli-odpoledne-40319537 |title=Francie pacienty do Brna nepo\u0161le, situaci u\u017e zvl\u00e1d\u00e1 l\u00e9pe |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Foreign aid to the Czech Republic'''\n*'''Taiwan''': Taiwan donated 25 lung ventilators to hospitals in the Czech Republic at the beginning of April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|author=Yang Xiaohong / Zuma Press / Profimedia |url=https://hlidacipes.org/darovane-rousky-z-ciny-jsou-pry-na-ceste-dorazi-pozdeji-nez-jinam-do-evropy-zato-i-s-krteckem/ |title=Darovan\u00e9 rou\u0161ky z \u010c\u00edny jsou pr\u00fd na cest\u011b. Doraz\u00ed pozd\u011bji ne\u017e jinam do Evropy, zato i s krte\u010dkem \u2013 Hl\u00eddac\u00edPes.org |publisher=Hlidacipes.org |date= |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n</div></div>\n'''1 April''' \u2013\nOne month ago the Czech Republic reported the first coronavirus case. A second senior from the Litom\u011b\u0159ice retirement home died, as well as seniors from Prague and [[Moravia-Silesia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pragueresident.com/caseupdate/ |title=The latest updates on Coronavirus in the Czech Republic |work=Prague Resident Magazine |date=15 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The Department of Infectious Diseases of the Central Military Hospital in Prague has treated COVID-19 patients with [[hydroxychloroquine]]. Eight of them have already been released for home quarantine. The evaluation of preliminary results of this therapy will be carried out in April. [[Chloroquine]] and hydroxychloroquine were originally used to treat [[malaria]], but at present they also help patients with [[autoimmune diseases]]\u2014[[rheumatoid arthritis]] or [[systemic lupus]]. The World Health Organization (WHO) considers these substances as one of the options to treat COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor: <!-- Pole autor --> \u010cTK |url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/v-uvn-zacali-podavat-pacientum-s-covid-19-hydroxychlorochin/1874596 |title=V \u00daVN za\u010dali pod\u00e1vat pacient\u016fm s COVID-19 hydroxychlorochin |work=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny |date=1 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''2 April''' \u2013\nOne victim died at the General University Hospital in Prague (VFN); another victim was a 79-year-old patient hospitalised at the [[Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9]] University Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor: <!-- Pole autor --> \u010cTK |url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/s-nemoci-covid-19-v-cr-zemrelo-44-lidi-uzdravilo-se-67-pacientu-/1874646 |title=S nemoc\u00ed COVID-19 v \u010cR zem\u0159elo 44 lid\u00ed, uzdravilo se 67 pacient\u016f |work=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny |date=2 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> The government decided to extend the border control by 20 days. Border checks with Germany and Austria will last until midnight Friday, 24 April.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor: <!-- Pole autor --> \u010cTK |url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/ochrana-hranic-s-nemeckem-a-rakouskem-potrva-do-pulnoci-24-dubna/1874653 |title=Ochrana hranic s N\u011bmeckem a Rakouskem potrv\u00e1 do p\u016flnoci 24. dubna |work=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny |date=2 April 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''3 April''' \u2013\nA public controversy has arisen around shipments of personal protective equipment that the Czech Government purchased and airlifted from China. On 31 March, Mayor of Prague publicly praised Government of Taiwan for donating ICU ventilators to the Czech Republic, while pointing out that all of the equipment from China was purchased, none was donated. Representatives of China's business interest in the Czech Republic countered by claiming that China donated personal protective equipment that was to be handed over to Czech hospitals on 1 April. According the media, Czech authorities received a promise of donation of PPE, however none have reached the country by 3 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|author=Yang Xiaohong / Zuma Press / Profimedia |url=https://hlidacipes.org/darovane-rousky-z-ciny-jsou-pry-na-ceste-dorazi-pozdeji-nez-jinam-do-evropy-zato-i-s-krteckem/?fbclid=IwAR0oIqSrBK8chGJroW6MN6-o3eosSkDhkPygP7SbPmAdj8SMiJXPpU2uIFU |title=Darovan\u00e9 rou\u0161ky z \u010c\u00edny jsou pr\u00fd na cest\u011b. Doraz\u00ed pozd\u011bji ne\u017e jinam do Evropy, zato i s krte\u010dkem \u2013 Hl\u00eddac\u00edPes.org |publisher=Hlidacipes.org |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''4 April''' \u2013 There were 29 infected police officers in the Czech Republic, 343 more were in preventative quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/umrti-s-nemoci-covid-19-pribylo-v-cesku-na-59-uzdravenych-je-78/1875645 |title=\u00damrt\u00ed s nemoc\u00ed covid-19 p\u0159ibylo v \u010cesku na 59, uzdraven\u00fdch je 78 |work=\u010cesk\u00e9 Noviny |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Week 15 (6 \u2013 12 April )===\n'''6 April''' \u2013 Government eased a number of restrictive measures, e.g. by opening outside sporting grounds (including skiing, shooting ranges, etc.), movement in parks and nature without facemasks and opening of more shops and services (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]).\n\n'''7 April''' \u2013 Government sought extension of the State of Emergency for 30 days, i.e. until 12 May 2020. Chamber of Deputies of Parliament granted extension until 30 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kate\u0159ina Frouzov\u00e1 |url=https://archiv.ihned.cz/c1-66747930-stav-nouze-potrva-do-kvetna |title=\u017div\u011b: Druh\u00fd den mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e9 sn\u011bmovny. Prodlou\u017een\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu Babi\u0161 neprosadil, pomoc \u017eivnostn\u00edk\u016fm pro\u0161la |work=Hospod\u00e1\u0159sk\u00e9 noviny |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''12 April''' \u2013 Government announced that it was prepairing a plan for gradual lifting of remaining restrictions. Government aimed at reaching maximum of 400 newly infected people a day in order toe prevent overburdening healthcare system. Instead of general restrictions, the indended maximum number should be reached through contact tracing of positive cases (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]). <ref>{{cite web | author=\u010cTK | title=Vl\u00e1da nebude uvol\u0148ovat restrikce p\u0159i 400 nov\u011b naka\u017een\u00fdch denn\u011b | website=Forum24 \u2013 Internetov\u00fd den\u00edk pro \u0161\u00ed\u0159en\u00ed svobodn\u00fdch informac\u00ed a kritickou diskusi | date=2020-04-12 | url=https://www.forum24.cz/vlada-nebude-uvolnovat-opatreni-pri-rustu-400-infikovanych-denne/ | language=cs | access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n===Week 16 (13 \u2013 19 April )===\n'''13 April''' \u2013 Number of COVID19 tests sank from 8,000 a day to mere 3,200 a day during Easter weekend which included also Friday and Monday as state holiday. According to health authority, testing capacity during Easter weekend significantly surpassed demand for testing from potential patients. Health authority expected the demand to rise again in the following week. <ref>{{cite web|author=Hana V\u00e1lkov\u00e1 |url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/testovani-covid-test-vikend-velikonoce-volno-pacient-koronavirus.A200413_170147_domaci_hv |title=Nez\u00e1jem lid\u00ed, m\u00e9n\u011b laborato\u0159\u00ed. Pro\u010d o v\u00edkendech a sv\u00e1tc\u00edch pad\u00e1 po\u010det test\u016f |publisher=iDNES.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n'''14 April''' \u2013 A month-long complete border closure ended (see [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic#Policies to fight the contagion|policies section below]]). A large number of [[Romani people in the Czech Republic|Czech Romanis]] started returning from particularly hit United Kingdom, where many lived for over 15 years, leading to fear of possible increase of COVID19 infection.<ref>https://www.idnes.cz/usti/zpravy/onemocneni-covid-19-romove-britanie-karantena.A200411_543163_usti-zpravy_pakr</ref> \n\n[[Hyundai]] factory in [[No\u0161ovice]], which makes 1,500 cars a day including [[Hyundai Kona|Kona Electric]], restarted production after three weeks pause. Manufacturing plants were unaffected by Government restrictions, however many had decided to close voluntarily.<ref>{{cite web | title=Automobilka Hyundai obnovila v\u00fdrobu v No\u0161ovic\u00edch, odst\u00e1vka trvala t\u0159i t\u00fddny | website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz - V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje | date=2020-04-14 | url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/ekonomika/automobilka-hyundai-po-odstavce-obnovila-vyrobu-v-nosovicich/r~7c0de98e7e1111ea842f0cc47ab5f122/ | language=cs | access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n\n<div class=\"toccolours\" style=\"width:1000px; margin:1em 0;\"><center>'''Current active cases and hospitalisation'''</center>\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=0.5\n|showSymbols=true\n|width=600\n|height=400\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date \n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend= Legend \